A. General Remarks

The text of this edition of the Planciana is founded mainly upon that of Kayser as given in Vol. V of the excellent edition of Cicero's works (edited by Baiter and Kayser and published by B. G. Tauclinitz, Leipzig, 1862). There is not much difference between the text of their edition and that of Baiter in Orelli's Cicero ed. 2, Zurieh 1856: in matters however of orthography it is generally considered superior.
